<HTMLInputElementFormNoValidate>
<summary>
The <strong><c>formNoValidate</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLInputElement"/> interface is a boolean value indicating if the {{htmlelement("form")}} will bypass <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Constraint_validation">constraint validation</see> when submitted via the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input">input</see>. It reflects the <c>&amp;lt;input&amp;gt;</c> element&amp;apos;s <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#formnovalidate"><c>formnovalidate</c></see> attribute.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>This property is valid only for <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/submit"><c>submit</c></see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/image"><c>image</c></see> <c>&amp;lt;input&amp;gt;</c> elements.</para><para>Its value overrides the <see cref="HTMLFormElement.NoValidate"/> property of the <see cref="HTMLFormElement"/> interface if the form is submitted via the input. This property can be retrieved or set.</para>
<para>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.ReportValidity"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.CheckValidity"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.FormAction"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.FormEnctype"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.FormMethod"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.FormTarget"/><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/submit"><c>&amp;lt;input type=&amp;quot;submit&amp;quot;&amp;gt;</c></see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/image"><c>&amp;lt;input type=&amp;quot;image&amp;quot;&amp;gt;</c></see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/form">form</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLFormElement.NoValidate"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLButtonElement.FormNoValidate"/><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn_web_development/Extensions/Forms/Form_validation">Learn: Client-side form validation</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Constraint_validation">Guide: Constraint validation</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLInputElement/formNoValidate"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A boolean.</value>
</HTMLInputElementFormNoValidate>
